###Finding the $\sin$ ratio

$\begin{align}
\sin\left( \dfrac{\pi}{3}\right) &= \dfrac{\text{opposite side length}}{\text{hypotenuse length}}\\\\
&= \dfrac{5\sqrt{3}}{10}\\\\
&=\dfrac{\sqrt{3}}{2}
\end{align}$

###Finding the $\sin$ ratio

$\begin{align}
\sin\left( \dfrac{\pi}{6}\right) &= \dfrac{\text{opposite side length}}{\text{hypotenuse length}}\\\\
&= \dfrac{6}{12}\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{2}
\end{align}$

###Finding the $\cos$ ratio

$\begin{align}
\cos\left( \dfrac{\pi}{3}\right) &= \dfrac{\text{adjacent side length}}{\text{hypotenuse length}}\\\\
&= \dfrac{9}{18}\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{2}
\end{align}$

###Finding the $\cos$ ratio

$\begin{align}
\cos\left( \dfrac{\pi}{6}\right) &= \dfrac{\text{adjacent side length}}{\text{hypotenuse length}}\\\\
&= \dfrac{7\sqrt{3}}{14}\\\\
&=\dfrac{\sqrt{3}}{2}
\end{align}$

###Finding the $\tan$ ratio

$\begin{align}
\tan\left( \dfrac{\pi}{3}\right) &= \dfrac{\text{opposite side length}}{\text{adjacent side length}}\\\\
&= \dfrac{4\sqrt{3}}{4}\\\\
&=\sqrt{3}
\end{align}$
